Class 48 25/09/2025

Network Teaming Configuration
==============================

Step1: Install teamd package if not available
	# yum install teamd -y

Step2: Run nmcli commands to configure teaming
	# nmcli conn add type team con-name team1 ifname team1 config '{"runner":{"name":"activebackup"}}'
	# nmcli conn add type team-slave con-name ens38 ifname ens38 master team0
	# nmcli conn add type team-slave con-name ens39 ifname ens39 master team0

Step3: Modify IP, Gateway and other Network details
	# nmcli conn modify team0 ipv4.addresses 192.168.29.168/24
	# nmcli conn mod team0 ipv4.gateway 192.168.29.1
	# nmcli conn mod team0 ipv4.dns 192.168.168.1
	# nmcli conn modify team0 ipv4.method manual

Step4: Restart all nic's along with teaming NIC
	# nmcli conn down ens38 && nmcli conn up ens38
	# nmcli conn down ens39 && nmcli conn up ens39
	# nmcli conn down team0 && nmcli conn up team0

Step5: Verify the teaming configuration
	# teamdctl team0 state view
	# ip addr
